16/Mar/26 5:51 AM;712020:19109706-a11c-4efd-abee-5ca72d900e45;[~accountid:712020:4adb279c-383d-4a86-b512-a5a829380b9f] [~accountid:712020:9881bb6e-cbf7-47a6-bf7a-838a383b2866] 

* To upload files in temp S3 bucket you can use the existing api endpoint {{/s3/url}} for batch upload {{/s3/urls/batch}} with {{operation: write}} to get the s3 presigned url and for bucket name pass “temp_photos” to upload it to TEMP_BUCKET, get the presigned url and upload files
* To extract the nameplats data from images, you can call below apis
** /extraction/extract-temp-nameplate-data – POST
** Request Body:
** {noformat}{
        "photos": ["https://pgz-s3-temp-photos.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/path/photo.jpg", ...],
        "node_class_id": "uuid",
        "core_attributes": [...],       // optional, for voltage context
        "overwrite_existing": false,     // optional, default false
        "extract_name": false,           // optional, if true AI will generate asset name
        "extract_subtype": false,        // optional, if true AI will determine subtype
        "subtype_options": [...]         // required if extract_subtype is true
    }{noformat}
** Response:
** {noformat}  {
    "extracted_attributes": [
        {
            "id": "1e11adf9-5f70-48e2-85f4-e7b55c7269ab",
