column41:
h3. Summary

We are migrating {{pre_dedup}} and {{post_dedup}} JSON data from the RDS instance to S3 to optimize database performance and handle large sync payloads. New S3 buckets are required across all environments.

h3. Context

The migration aims to improve database performance by storing large sync payloads in S3. New S3 buckets need to be provisioned in Dev, Stage, and Prod environments.

h3. Acceptance criteria

* Provision new S3 buckets in all environments:
** *Dev:* {{eg-pz-dev-s3-sync-jobs-ohio}}
** *QA:* {{eg-pz-qa-s3-sync-jobs-ohio}}
** *Stage:* {{eg-pz-stage-s3-sync-jobs-ohio}}
** *Prod:* {{eg-pz-prod-s3-sync-jobs-ohio}}
* Ensure the bucket naming follows the standard naming pattern.
* Add a new environment variable in the backend for the bucket name:
** {{S3_BUCKET_SYNC_JOBS}}

h3. Other information

N/A

Add two non-nullable boolean columns to the {{issues}} table and document the {{details}} JSONB field as a validated structural contract enforced at the API layer.

----

*Schema Migration*

{code:sql}ALTER TABLE issues
  ADD COLUMN immediate_hazard   BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
  ADD COLUMN customer_notified  BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE;{code}

----

{{details}} JSONB Contract _(API-layer enforced on write)_

{code:json}{
  "consequences": {
    "equipment_failure":   false,
    "fire_hazard":         false,
    "safety_hazard":       false,
    "power_interruption":  false,
    "description":         ""
  },
  "corrective_action": {
    "fixed_during_visit":      false,
    "contractor_will_correct": false,
    "customer_will_correct":   false,
    "estimate_required":       false
  }
}{code}

----

*Work Required*

# Write Alembic migration for the two new columns
# Update SQLAlchemy {{Issue}} model with {{immediate_hazard}} and {{customer_notified}}
# Add JSONB structure validation to the API write path for {{details}}
# Verify migration executes cleanly against dev DB with no data loss

----

*Acceptance Criteria*

* {{immediate_hazard}} and {{customer_notified}} added as non-nullable booleans defaulting to {{false}}
* {{details}} JSONB enforces documented structure on write, validated at API layer
* Alembic migration created and tested against dev DB
* SQLAlchemy model updated to reflect new columns and JSONB structure

