h2. Description

Two UX improvements for the SLD (Single Line Diagram) component:

# Escape key to cancel selection - Clear all selections and close context menus when pressing Escape
# Auto-select expanded nodes - After "Expand Clean" (Shift+E) operation, automatically select all newly expanded downstream nodes for immediate follow-up operations

h2. Technical Documentation

h3. File to modify

eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/GraphEditor.jsx

h3. Feature 1: Escape Key to Cancel Selection

1.1 Add clearAllSelections to destructured values from useSelectionHandlers (line ~2217)

1.2 Add Escape handler to the handleNodeKeyDown useEffect (line ~2464):

{code:javascript}// Escape - Cancel selection and close context menus
if (event.key === 'Escape') {
  event.preventDefault();
  clearAllSelections();
  closeContextMenu();
  setSelectionMode(false);
  setSelectionBox(null);
  setFirstTapPosition(null);
}{code}

This will: clear all node/edge selections, close any open context menus, exit area selection mode, clear the selection box visual, and reset first tap position.

1.3 Update the dependency array for the useEffect (line ~2676) - add clearAllSelections, closeContextMenu, setSelectionMode, setSelectionBox, and setFirstTapPosition.

h3. Feature 2: Auto-select Expanded Nodes After Expand Clean

The handleExpandClean function (lines 356-534) expands collapsed nodes and repositions them. Currently it does not select the newly expanded nodes.

2.1 Track expanded node IDs in handleExpandClean (line ~400-450). Add a Set to collect all expanded node IDs:

{code:javascript}const allExpandedNodeIds = new Set();

// Then for each target node:
const downstreamNodeIds = expandClean(targetNodeId);
downstreamNodeIds.forEach(id => allExpandedNodeIds.add(id));{code}

2.2 Select expanded nodes after position updates complete (line ~500-530):

{code:javascript}// Select the newly expanded nodes
if (allExpandedNodeIds.size > 0) {
  setNodes(currentNodes =>
    currentNodes.map(node => ({
      ...node,
      selected: allExpandedNodeIds.has(node.id)
    }))
  );
}{code}

h3. Verification

Feature 1 Test Cases (Escape key):

* Select a node, press Escape → node should be deselected
* Select multiple nodes (Shift+click), press Escape → all nodes deselected
* Right-click a node to open context menu, press Escape → menu closes
* Select an edge, press Escape → edge deselected

Feature 2 Test Cases (Auto-select after expand):

* Collapse a node with downstream nodes
* Run "Expand Clean" (Shift+E) on the collapsed node
* Verify: all newly expanded downstream nodes are automatically selected
* Verify: can immediately perform operations on selected nodes (e.g., straighten with 's')

