column41:
h2. Optimization - Effect Cleanup

h2. Problem

* Current effect dependencies include unnecessary items causing extra executions
* Effect runs even when view hasn't actually changed
* Missing early return for same-view transitions

h2. Scope

* Audit useEffect dependencies (Lines 3296-3348)
* Add early return when {{previousViewId === activeViewId}}
* Remove unnecessary dependencies: {{setNodes}}, {{reactFlowInstance}}
* Use refs for stable values that shouldn't trigger re-runs

h2. Current Code Issue

{code:javascript}useEffect(() => {
  // Executes on EVERY view change
  // Processes ALL nodes in the graph
  // Performs expensive position calculations
  // Triggers complete state updates
}, [activeViewId, viewMappings, setNodes, baseNodesReady, reactFlowInstance, flowOnlyMode]);{code}

h2. Implementation Details

{code:javascript}useEffect(() => {
  if (!flowOnlyMode || !baseNodesReady) return;

  const previousViewId = prevActiveViewIdRef.current;
  // Early return if view hasn't changed
  if (previousViewId === activeViewId && previousViewId !== null) return;

  prevActiveViewIdRef.current = activeViewId;

  // ... rest of transformation logic
}, [activeViewId, baseNodesReady, flowOnlyMode]); // Reduced dependencies{code}

h2. Acceptance Criteria

* [ ] Effect only runs when view actually changes
* [ ] Reduce unnecessary effect executions
* [ ] Document remaining required dependencies
* [ ] No regression in view switching functionality
* [ ] Unit tests for effect trigger conditions

h2. Technical Reference

* [Performance Optimisation: GraphEditor View Transformation|https://egalvanic.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ENGR/pages/72024086]
* Related: ZP-496

h2. Phase 2 - Memory Optimization

h2. Problem

* Extensive object spreading creates garbage collection pressure
* Temporary arrays and objects accumulate rapidly
* Browser pauses for GC during interactions
* ReactFlow's internal optimizations are bypassed

h2. Scope

* Replace {{{ ...node.position }}} with direct assignment when possible
* Implement shallow comparison for position changes before updating
* Avoid creating new node objects when position unchanged
* Use {{React.memo}} or {{useMemo}} where appropriate for node components

h2. Implementation Details

{code:javascript}// Position equality check utility
const hasPositionChanged = (pos1, pos2) => {
  return pos1.x !== pos2.x || pos1.y !== pos2.y;
};

// Only update nodes with actual changes
setNodes(current => {
  return current.map(node => {
    const base = baseNodesMap.get(node.id);
    if (!base) return node;

    // Only update if position changed
    if (node.position.x === base.position.x && 
        node.position.y === base.position.y) {
      return node; // Return same reference
    }

    return { ...node, position: { ...base.position } };
  });
});{code}

h2. Benefits

* Reduced object allocations during view transformation
* Better cache locality
* Reduced GC pressure

h2. Acceptance Criteria

* [ ] Reduce object allocations during view transformation
* [ ] Only update nodes with actual position changes
* [ ] Implement position equality check utility
* [ ] Memory profiling shows reduced GC pressure
* [ ] Unit tests for comparison utilities

h2. Technical Reference

* [Performance Optimisation: GraphEditor View Transformation|https://egalvanic.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ENGR/pages/72024086]
* Related: ZP-496

h2. Phase 3 - Scalability

h2. Problem

* Complete node array replacement triggers re-render of all node components
* Even nodes with unchanged positions re-render
* Large graphs cause noticeable UI freeze

h2. Scope

* Create {{performIncrementalUpdate}} function with configurable batch size (default: 50)
* Process node updates across multiple animation frames
* Track update progress and handle partial updates gracefully
* Add visual feedback during batch processing (optional loading indicator)

h2. Implementation Details

{code:javascript}const performIncrementalUpdate = (nodeIds, batchSize = 50) => {
  let currentIndex = 0;

  const processBatch = () => {
    const batch = nodeIds.slice(currentIndex, currentIndex + batchSize);

    setNodes(currentNodes => {
      const updates = new Map();
      batch.forEach(id => {
        const mapping = mappingsMap.get(id);
        if (mapping) updates.set(id, mapping);
      });

      return currentNodes.map(node => 
        updates.has(node.id) 
          ? { ...node, position: updates.get(node.id) }
          : node
      );
    });

    currentIndex += batchSize;
    if (currentIndex < nodeIds.length) {
      requestAnimationFrame(processBatch);
    }
  };

  processBatch();
};{code}

h2. Benefits

* Spreads computational load across frames
* Prevents UI freezing
* Maintains interactivity during updates

h2. Acceptance Criteria

* [ ] Implement batched node position updates
* [ ] Configurable batch size for tuning
* [ ] No UI freezing with 1000+ nodes
* [ ] Graceful handling of interrupted updates
* [ ] Unit tests for batch processing logic

h2. Technical Reference

* [Performance Optimisation: GraphEditor View Transformation|https://egalvanic.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ENGR/pages/72024086]
* Related: ZP-496
* Depends on: Ticket 2 (Deferred Updates)

h2. Phase 2 - Non-blocking UI

h2. Problem

* All position calculations execute synchronously on the main thread
* React's reconciliation is blocked during transformation
* UI becomes unresponsive during large graph operations

h2. Scope

* Wrap view transformation logic with {{requestIdleCallback}}
* Use {{requestAnimationFrame}} for viewport fitting after updates
* Add polyfill for {{requestIdleCallback}} for browser compatibility
* Implement timeout fallback (100ms) to ensure updates complete

h2. Implementation Details

{code:javascript}useEffect(() => {
  if (!flowOnlyMode || !baseNodesReady) return;

  const previousViewId = prevActiveViewIdRef.current;
  if (previousViewId === activeViewId && previousViewId !== null) return;

  prevActiveViewIdRef.current = activeViewId;

  // Defer expensive operations to next frame
  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    requestIdleCallback(() => {
      performViewTransformation(activeViewId, previousViewId);
    }, { timeout: 100 });
  });
}, [activeViewId, baseNodesReady, flowOnlyMode]);{code}

h2. Benefits

* Non-blocking: UI remains responsive
* Leverages the browser's idle time
* Maintains 60 FPS during interactions

h2. Acceptance Criteria

* [ ] View transformation no longer blocks main thread
* [ ] UI remains responsive during view switching with 500+ nodes
* [ ] Add {{requestIdleCallback}} polyfill if needed
* [ ] Maintain 60 FPS during drag operations
* [ ] Unit tests for deferred update mechanism

h2. Technical Reference

* [Performance Optimisation: GraphEditor View Transformation|https://egalvanic.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ENGR/pages/72024086]
* Related: ZP-496
* Depends on: Ticket 1 (Data Structures Optimization)

h2. Phase 1 - Foundation

h2. Problem

* Current implementation uses {{Array.find()}} resulting in O(n²) complexity
* Base nodes synchronization (Lines 3299-3334) performs linear search for each node
* Position mapping application (Lines 3340-3347) has another linear search per node

h2. Scope

* Create {{baseNodesMap}} using {{useMemo}} for O(1) node lookups
* Optimize {{syncPositionsOptimized}} to use Map instead of repeated array searches
* Add {{hasPositionChanged}} utility to skip unnecessary updates
* Cache {{viewFilteredNodes}} computation with {{useMemo}}

h2. Implementation Details

{code:javascript}// Use Map instead of repeated array searches
const baseNodesMap = useMemo(() => {
  const map = new Map();
  baseNodesRef.current.forEach(node => map.set(node.id, node));
  return map;
}, [baseNodesRef.current]);

// Optimize position synchronization
const syncPositionsOptimized = (currentNodes) => {
  currentNodes.forEach(node => {
    const baseNode = baseNodesMap.get(node.id);
    if (baseNode && hasPositionChanged(node.position, baseNode.position)) {
      baseNode.position = { x: node.position.x, y: node.position.y };
    }
  });
};

// Cache computed values
const viewFilteredNodes = useMemo(() => {
  if (activeViewId === 'all') return baseNodesRef.current;

  const viewNodeIds = new Set(
    viewMappings
      .filter(m => m.sld_view_id === activeViewId && !m.is_deleted)
      .map(m => m.node_id)
  );

  return baseNodesRef.current.filter(node => viewNodeIds.has(node.id));
}, [activeViewId, viewMappings]);{code}

h2. Acceptance Criteria

* [ ] Replace all {{Array.find()}} calls with Map lookups in view transformation
* [ ] Add memoized {{baseNodesMap}} for node lookup optimization
* [ ] Implement position change detection to avoid unnecessary updates
* [ ] Unit tests for optimized data structures
* [ ] Performance test: View switching with 500+ nodes should show measurable improvement

h2. Technical Reference

* [Performance Optimisation: GraphEditor View Transformation|https://egalvanic.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ENGR/pages/72024086]
* Related: ZP-496

