{{- Simplify job assignment dialog}}

h1. Plan: Replace Autocomplete with Select + Custom Option for Core Attributes

h2. Summary

Modify the {{selectFieldView}} in {{EntityCoreAttributesRowView.swift}} to use a native iOS Menu-based dropdown instead of an autocomplete text field, with a "Custom" option that switches to a text input when selected.

h2. Current Behavior

* Uses an autocomplete pattern with a text field that filters options as user types
* Options appear in a dropdown below the text field
* Works but feels less "flow-y" than native selects

h2. Target Behavior

# *Default*: Native iOS Menu dropdown showing all predefined options
# *Custom Option*: At the bottom, separated by a light border/divider, show "Custom" option
# *Custom Mode*: When "Custom" clicked, switch UI to a text input field
# *Clear Button*: When value exists (in either mode), show a clear button (x)
# *Clear Resets Mode*: Clearing the value switches back to select mode

h2. File to Modify

{{/Users/ericehlert/projects/eg-pz/eg-pz-mobile-iOS/Egalvanic PZ/Core/UI/Views/EntityCoreAttributesRowView.swift}}

h2. Implementation Details

h3. 1. Add State Variable (around line 17)

Add a new state variable to track custom input mode:

{code:swift}@State private var isCustomMode: Bool = false{code}

h3. 2. Update Initializer (around line 23)

Set initial {{isCustomMode}} based on whether current value matches any predefined option:

{code:swift}// Determine if current value is a custom value (not in options list)
let options = classProperty.options.compactMap { $0 }
let isCustom = !currentValue.isEmpty && !options.contains(currentValue)
self._isCustomMode = State(initialValue: isCustom){code}

h3. 3. Replace {{selectFieldView}} (lines 199-285)

Replace with new implementation:

{code:swift}private var selectFieldView: some View {
    let options = classProperty.options.compactMap { $0 }

    return VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 4) {
        HStack(spacing: 4) {
            Text(classProperty.name)
                .font(.caption)
                .foregroundColor(.secondary)
            afRequiredBadge
            Spacer()
        }

        if isCustomMode {
            // Custom text input mode
            HStack {
                TextField("Enter custom value...", text: $localValue)
                    .onChange(of: localValue) { _, newValue in
                        debouncedValueChange(newValue)
                    }

                // Clear button - clears and returns to select mode
                Button(action: {
                    localValue = ""
                    immediateValueChange("")
                    isCustomMode = false
                }) {
                    Image(systemName: "xmark.circle.fill")
                        .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                        .font(.caption)
                }
            }
            .padding(.horizontal, 12)
            .padding(.vertical, 8)
            .background(Color(.systemGray6))
            .cornerRadius(8)
        } else {
            // Select mode with Menu dropdown
            Menu {
                // Predefined options
                ForEach(options, id: \.self) { option in
                    Button(action: {
                        localValue = option
                        immediateValueChange(option)
                    }) {
                        HStack {
                            Text(option)
                            if localValue == option {
                                Spacer()
                                Image(systemName: "checkmark")
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }

                // Separator and Custom option
                Divider()

                Button(action: {
                    isCustomMode = true
                    localValue = ""
                    immediateValueChange("")
                }) {
                    HStack {
                        Text("Custom")
                            .italic()
                        Image(systemName: "pencil")
                    }
                }
            } label: {
                HStack {
                    Text(localValue.isEmpty ? "Select..." : localValue)
                        .foregroundColor(localValue.isEmpty ? .secondary : .primary)

                    Spacer()

                    // Clear button (only when value exists)
                    if !localValue.isEmpty {
                        Button(action: {
                            localValue = ""
                            immediateValueChange("")
                        }) {
                            Image(systemName: "xmark.circle.fill")
                                .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                                .font(.caption)
                        }
                    }

                    Image(systemName: "chevron.down")
                        .font(.caption)
                        .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                }
                .padding(.horizontal, 12)
                .padding(.vertical, 8)
                .background(Color(.systemGray6))
                .cornerRadius(8)
            }
        }
    }
}{code}

h3. 4. Remove Unused Code

Delete {{computeFilteredOptions()}} function (lines 287-303) as it's no longer needed.

h2. Edge Cases Handled

# *Existing custom value*: If a node/edge/issue already has a custom value that doesn't match any predefined option, it will start in custom mode
# *Empty value*: Shows "Select..." placeholder and is in select mode
# *Clear from custom mode*: Clears value AND switches back to select mode
# *Clear from select mode*: Just clears value, stays in select mode

h2. Visual Design

* *Select mode*: Native iOS Menu dropdown (matches other pickers in the app like {{TerminalPicker}})
* *Custom option*: Italicized "Custom" text with pencil icon, separated by Divider
* *Custom mode*: Standard text input with clear button
* *Clear button*: {{xmark.circle.fill}} icon, secondary color

h2. Verification

# Open the app and navigate to edit a node with core attributes that have select-type properties
# Verify the dropdown shows predefined options
# Verify "Custom" appears at the bottom with a divider
# Click "Custom" and verify it switches to text input
# Enter a custom value and save
# Clear the value and verify it returns to select mode
# Test same behavior on edges and issues

h1. Plan: Sort Node/Enclosure Classes Alphabetically in Dropdowns

h2. Problem

The "+ Asset" and "+ Box" dropdowns in the web view display node classes and enclosure classes in the order returned by the API, which is not alphabetical. Users expect alphabetical ordering for easier scanning.

h2. Solution

Sort the class arrays alphabetically by {{name}} before mapping them to dropdown items in both selector components.

h2. Files to Modify

h3. 1. {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/NodeTypeSelector.jsx}}

*Current behavior (lines 55-56):*

{code:javascript}const ocpClasses = nodeClasses.filter((cls) => cls.ocp === true);
const otherClasses = nodeClasses.filter((cls) => cls.ocp !== true);{code}

*Change:* Add {{.sort()}} after each filter to sort alphabetically by name:

{code:javascript}const ocpClasses = nodeClasses
  .filter((cls) => cls.ocp === true)
  .sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
const otherClasses = nodeClasses
  .filter((cls) => cls.ocp !== true)
  .sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));{code}

h3. 2. {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/BoxTypeSelector.jsx}}

*Current behavior (line 48):*

{code:javascript}const boxClasses = classes.filter((cls) => cls.box === true);{code}

*Change:* Add {{.sort()}} after filter:

{code:javascript}const boxClasses = classes
  .filter((cls) => cls.box === true)
  .sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));{code}

h2. Verification

# Start the frontend dev server: {{cd eg-pz-frontend && npm run dev}}
# Navigate to an SLD view
# Click "+ Asset" button - verify classes are alphabetically sorted within each category (Overcurrent Protection, Other Equipment)
# Click "+ Box" button - verify enclosure classes are alphabetically sorted

h1. Plan: iOS WebView SLD Fixes

h2. Issue 1: Double-Click Zoom on Connection Mode

h3. Problem

When double-clicking nodes in the embedded iOS app to enter connection mode, an unintended zoom occurs.

h3. Root Cause

{{handleNodeConnectionClick}} only receives the {{node}} parameter, not the {{event}}. We can't call {{event.stopPropagation()}} to prevent the iOS WebView's zoom gesture.

h3. Solution

Pass the event object to {{handleNodeConnectionClick}} and call {{stopPropagation()}} when a double-tap is detected.

h3. Files to Modify

*1.* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/hooks/useConnectionMode.jsx}}

Line 231-232 - Add event parameter:

{noformat}const handleNodeConnectionClick = useCallback(
  (node, event) => {{noformat}

Lines 243-245 - Stop propagation after double-tap detected:

{noformat}// Double tap detected
clearTimeout(doubleTapTimerRef.current);
doubleTapTimerRef.current = null;

// Prevent zoom behavior in iOS WebView
if (event) {
  event.stopPropagation();
}{noformat}

*2.* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/GraphEditor.jsx}}

Line 2815 - Pass event:

{noformat}const connectionResult = handleNodeConnectionClick(node, event);{noformat}

----

h2. Issue 2: Busway Node Double Outline

h3. Problem

Busway nodes have a weird second outline that other node types don't have.

h3. Root Cause

CSS styling uses a whitelist approach - each node type must be explicitly added to get {{padding: 0 !important; border: none;}}. New node types (like busway) get missed.

h3. Solution

Flip to a default approach: apply clean styling to ALL nodes, only override for exceptions (like {{sldLink}} if needed in future).

h3. Files to Modify

*1.* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/nodes/NodeStyles.css}}

Add universal rule at line ~132 (before the grouped selectors):

