h1. Implementation Plan: Instance-Level Terminal Rendering

h2. Overview

This plan implements the architectural change from *blueprint-based terminals* (NodeOrientationTerminal) to *instance-level terminals* (NodeTerminal) for rendering handles on React Flow nodes, as described in PRODUCT_ARCHITECTURE.md Section 2.

h3. Why This Change?

# *Per-node terminal customization*: Each node can have different terminal configurations
# *Instance-specific electrical data*: Store voltage/amp ratings per terminal
# *Offline edge creation*: Terminal UUIDs enable proper edge FK resolution without network
# *Single source of truth*: Edge stores terminal UUID, handle_code is derived

----

h2. Current State Summary

||Component||Status||Details||
|Backend {{NodeTerminal}} model|✅ Exists|Missing {{position}}, {{offset_percent}}, {{color}}, {{show_label}} in {{to_dict()}}|
|Backend {{Node.to_dict()}}|✅ Complete|Already includes {{node_terminals}}|
|Backend SLD endpoints|✅ Complete|Already return {{node_terminals}} in node data|
|Frontend {{terminalHelpers.js}}|⚠️ Needs Update|Only reads blueprint terminals, not instance-level|
|Frontend node creation|⚠️ Needs Update|Does not create {{NodeTerminal}} instances|
|iOS {{NodeV2}} model|⚠️ Needs Update|Missing {{node_terminals}} relationship|
|iOS DTOs|⚠️ Needs Update|Node DTOs don't include {{node_terminals}}|

