h1. Plan: Update NodeClassPreview to Use Database Orientation Data

h2. Problem

{{NodeClassPreview.jsx}} has hardcoded handle positions for each orientation type (lines 92-159). This means:

* Preview won't match actual rendering if orientation terminals are modified in the database
* New orientations added to the database won't display correctly in the preview
* Terminal colors, labels, and positions in preview may differ from what DynamicNode renders

h2. Solution

Update {{NodeClassPreview}} to dynamically render handles based on actual {{orientation_terminals}} data from the database, matching how {{DynamicNode}} renders nodes.

h2. Backend Status (Verified - No Changes Needed)

The {{/node_orientations}} endpoint already returns {{orientation_terminals}} with all needed data:

* {{position}}: top | bottom | left | right
* {{offset_percent}}: 0-100 (percentage along the side)
* {{color}}: hex color string (e.g., "#666666")
* {{side}}: LINE (input/target) or LOAD (output/source)
* {{label}}: terminal label (e.g., "Normal", "Emergency")
* {{show_label}}: boolean

h2. Files to Modify (Frontend Only)

h3. 1. {{eg-pz-frontend/src/components/NodeClassPreview.jsx}}

* Accept {{orientationTerminals}} as a new prop (array of terminal objects)
* Remove hardcoded {{handles}} useMemo switch statement (lines 92-159)
* Dynamically render handles based on {{orientationTerminals}}:
** Use {{position}} for placement (top/bottom/left/right)
** Use {{offset_percent}} for positioning along the side
** Use {{color}} for handle color
** Use {{side}} (LINE=target, LOAD=source) for handle type indicator

h3. 2. {{eg-pz-frontend/src/components/AssetClassCreator.jsx}}

* When orientation is selected, find the matching orientation object from {{nodeOrientations}}
* Pass {{orientation.orientation_terminals}} to {{NodeClassPreview}}

h3. 3. {{eg-pz-frontend/src/components/AssetClassEditor.jsx}}

* When class data loads, extract orientation terminals from the class's orientation
* Pass {{orientation_terminals}} to {{NodeClassPreview}}

h2. Implementation Details

h3. NodeClassPreview Handle Rendering Logic

{noformat}// Convert orientation terminals to handle configs
const handles = useMemo(() => {
  if (!orientationTerminals?.length) {
    // Fallback to vertical default
    return { top: [{ type: 'target' }], bottom: [{ type: 'source' }] };
  }

  const result = { top: [], bottom: [], left: [], right: [] };
  orientationTerminals.forEach(terminal => {
    const handle = {
      type: terminal.side === 'LINE' ? 'target' : 'source',
      color: terminal.color || '#666666',
      offsetPercent: terminal.offset_percent || 50,
      label: terminal.label,
      showLabel: terminal.show_label,
    };
    if (terminal.position) {
      result[terminal.position].push(handle);
    }
  });
  return result;
}, [orientationTerminals]);{noformat}

h3. Handle Positioning (matching DynamicNode logic)

* For top handles: {{left: ${offsetPercent}%}}, {{top: -4px}}
* For bottom handles: {{left: ${offsetPercent}%}}, {{bottom: -4px}}
* For left handles: {{top: ${offsetPercent}%}}, {{left: -4px}}
* For right handles: {{top: ${offsetPercent}%}}, {{right: -4px}}

h3. Prop Changes for Parent Components

*AssetClassCreator.jsx:*

