h1. Plan: Add SLD View Mapping for Child Nodes Created from EditNodeDetailViewV3

h2. Problem Statement

When a child node is created from {{EditNodeDetailViewV3}} (accessed via web view with an active SLD view), the child node does NOT get added to {{mapping_node_sld_view}} for the active view.

*Result:* Child nodes created from the edit view don't appear in the SLD view they were created from.

*What already works:* {{parent_id}} is correctly set via {{NodeService.createChildNode()}} (line 818 in NodeService.swift).

h2. Root Cause

The active view context ({{selectedViewId}}) is available in {{WebAppContainerViewWithView}} but is NOT passed through the view hierarchy:

* {{WebAppContainerViewWithView.swift:232-234}} opens {{EditNodeDetailViewV3}} without view context
* {{EditNodeDetailViewV3}} opens {{CreateChildNodeView}} without view context
* {{CreateChildNodeView}} calls {{NodeService.createChildNode()}} with no view awareness

h2. Solution

Pass the active view ID through the view hierarchy and create the {{mapping_node_sld_view}} entry when a child node is created.

----

h2. Implementation Steps

h3. Step 1: Modify {{EditNodeDetailViewV3}} to Accept View Context

*File:* {{eg-pz-mobile-iOS/Egalvanic PZ/Views/Assets/EditNodeDetailView.swift}}

Add optional {{activeViewId}} parameter:

* Add property: {{let activeViewId: UUID?}}
* Add to init with default value {{nil}}
* Pass to {{CreateChildNodeView}} when presenting child creation

h3. Step 2: Modify {{CreateChildNodeView}} to Accept View Context

*File:* {{eg-pz-mobile-iOS/Egalvanic PZ/Views/Assets/CreateChildNodeView.swift}}

Add optional {{activeViewId}} parameter:

* Add property: {{let activeViewId: UUID?}}
* Modify {{createChild()}} to call a new method that creates the view mapping

h3. Step 3: Add View Mapping Creation Logic to {{CreateChildNodeView}}

In {{CreateChildNodeView.createChild()}}, after the node is created:

# If {{activeViewId}} is NOT nil, create a {{MappingNodeSLDView}} entry
# Use same pattern as {{linkNodeToSession()}} for online/offline sync

{code:swift}private func linkNodeToView(node: NodeV2, viewId: UUID) async {
    // Create local mapping
    let mapping = MappingNodeSLDView(
        id: UUID(),
        node_id: node.id,
        sld_view_id: viewId,
        x: 0,  // Child nodes have relative position within parent
        y: 0,
        width: node.width,
        height: node.height,
        is_collapsed: false,
        is_deleted: false,
        created_at: Date(),
        modified_at: Date()
    )
    modelContext.insert(mapping)
    try? modelContext.save()

    // Sync to server (online) or queue (offline)
    if networkState.mode == .online {
        do {
            _ = try await APIClient.shared.addNodeToView(
                viewId: viewId,
                nodeId: node.id,
                x: 0,
                y: 0,
                width: node.width,
                height: node.height
            )
        } catch {
            // Fall back to offline queue
            let syncService = SyncQueueService(modelContext: modelContext)
            syncService.enqueueNodeSLDViewCreate(...)
        }
    } else {
        let syncService = SyncQueueService(modelContext: modelContext)
        syncService.enqueueNodeSLDViewCreate(...)
    }
}{code}

