h1. ZP-610 Section 4: Edge Creation Flow - Implementation Plan

h2. Summary

Section 4 specifies that *terminal UUIDs should be the authoritative connection identifiers*, with handle_code strings derived at render time only. The current implementation uses handle_code strings throughout the pipeline, which works but doesn't align with the spec.

h2. Root Cause

The issue starts at the *frontend* - {{useConnectionMode.jsx}} creates edge objects with only {{sourceHandle}}/{{targetHandle}} (handle_code strings). It does NOT include {{source_node_terminal_id}}/{{target_node_terminal_id}}. This means:

* iOS never receives terminal UUIDs (because they're not sent)
* Backend has to resolve handle strings → terminal UUIDs

h2. Current State vs. Target State

||Component||Current||Target (Section 4)||
|{{terminalHelpers.js}}|Default terminal uses handle_code pattern|Filter by {{side}} (LINE/LOAD)|
|{{HandleSelectionModal}}|Returns handle_code string|Return terminal UUID|
|{{useConnectionMode.jsx}}|Passes handle strings|Pass terminal UUIDs; derive handles for React Flow|
|{{iosMessageHandlers.js}}|Sends sourceHandle/targetHandle|Send terminal UUIDs only|
|iOS {{WebViewBridge}}|Receives handle strings|Receive terminal UUIDs|
|iOS {{EdgeV2}} model|Has both handle strings + terminal UUIDs|Terminal UUIDs only (remove handle fields)|
|Backend Edge API|Resolves handles → terminals|Accept terminal UUIDs directly|

h2. Implementation Tasks

h3. 1. Frontend: Update {{terminalHelpers.js}}

*File*: {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/utils/terminalHelpers.js}}

Update default terminal selection to use {{side}} instead of handle_code pattern:

{code:javascript}export function getDefaultSourceTerminal(node) {
  const terminals = node?.data?.node_terminals || [];
  return terminals.find((t) => t.side === "LOAD" && !t.is_deleted);
}

export function getDefaultTargetTerminal(node) {
  const terminals = node?.data?.node_terminals || [];
  return terminals.find((t) => t.side === "LINE" && !t.is_deleted);
}{code}

