h1. Fix: Distribute Children Not Syncing to Backend

h2. Problem Summary

The "Distribute Children" feature crashes before reaching the backend sync code. The error at {{useSelectionHandlers.jsx:53}} is:

{noformat}Uncaught TypeError: (void 0) is not a function{noformat}

h2. Root Cause

In {{useSelectionHandlers.jsx}} line 53, the code calls {{iOSHandlers.sendMessage(...)}}, but {{sendMessage}} is a *private helper function* in {{iosMessageHandlers.js}} (line 14) - it's not exported.

The code crashes at line 53, which prevents the backend sync code (lines 92-102) from ever executing.

h2. Fix

h3. File: {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/hooks/useSelectionHandlers.jsx}}

*Lines 52-61* - Replace direct {{sendMessage}} call with the existing exported function {{sendEnclosureSizeUpdated}}:

{code:javascript}// BEFORE (crashes because sendMessage is not exported):
if (update.additionalFields?.width !== undefined || update.additionalFields?.height !== undefined) {
  iOSHandlers.sendMessage("graphUpdate", {
    type: "enclosureSizeUpdated",
    payload: {
      nodeId: update.nodeId,
      width: update.additionalFields?.width,
      height: update.additionalFields?.height
    }
  });
}

// AFTER (uses the properly exported function):
if (update.additionalFields?.width !== undefined || update.additionalFields?.height !== undefined) {
  iOSHandlers.sendEnclosureSizeUpdated(
    update.nodeId,
    update.additionalFields?.width,
    update.additionalFields?.height
  );
}{code}

That's it - one change to fix both the crash and the backend sync issue.

h2. Why This Works

# {{sendEnclosureSizeUpdated}} (line 94 of {{iosMessageHandlers.js}}) is already exported and does exactly what the broken code was trying to do
# Once the crash is fixed, the code will continue to lines 92-102 where {{putNodePosition}} is called for backend sync

