h1. SLD Links Implementation Plan for iOS Mobile App

h2. Problem Summary

SLD links aren't working in the iOS mobile app due to several issues:

# *Data transformation mismatch*: WebViewBridge passes raw link data but frontend expects view-perspective-transformed fields
# *Missing link navigation handler*: {{handleLinkNavigation}} in GraphEditor doesn't send iOS messages in flowOnlyMode
# *Missing APIClient routes*: No create/update/delete routes for SLD links in iOS
# *Missing "Create Link" UI*: No option in the More dropdown for flowOnlyMode
# *Missing position update handling*: Links can't be moved/repositioned via iOS

----

h2. Implementation Plan

h3. Phase 1: Fix Link Data Transformation (Critical - Fixes Display Issue)

*File:* {{eg-pz-mobile-iOS/Egalvanic PZ/Bridges/WebViewBridge.swift}}

The WebViewBridge builds {{linkDtos}} with raw fields from {{SLDLinkV2}}, but the frontend expects view-perspective-transformed fields. Need to transform links similar to how backend's {{get_links_for_view()}} does.

*Current (lines 309-327):*

{code:swift}var linkDto: [String: Any] = [
    "id": link.id.uuidString,
    "source_sld_view_id": link.source_sld_view_id.uuidString,
    "target_sld_view_id": link.target_sld_view_id.uuidString,
    // ... raw fields
]{code}

*Required transformation:*

{code:swift}// Determine perspective based on which view we're displaying
let isSourcePerspective = link.source_sld_view_id == activeViewId

var linkDto: [String: Any] = [
    "id": link.id.uuidString,
    // Position for current view
    "view_x": isSourcePerspective ? link.source_x : link.target_x,
    "view_y": isSourcePerspective ? link.source_y : link.target_y,
    // Node in this view that the link connects to
    "view_node_id": isSourcePerspective ? link.source_node_id : link.target_node_id,
    // Where the link navigates to
    "destination_view_id": isSourcePerspective ? link.target_sld_view_id : link.source_sld_view_id,
    "destination_node_id": isSourcePerspective ? link.target_node_id : link.source_node_id,
    // Display info
    "target_view_name": link.target_view_name,
    "target_node_label": link.target_node_label,
    "target_node_parent_label": link.target_node_parent_label,
    // Direction (flip if viewing from target perspective)
    "edge_direction": isSourcePerspective ? link.edge_direction : (link.edge_direction == "downstream" ? "upstream" : "downstream"),
    "view_perspective": isSourcePerspective ? "source" : "target",
    "is_deleted": link.is_deleted
]{code}

