*File:* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/GraphEditor.jsx}}

{color:#de350b}_PM NOTE: I don’t see any requirement here to define the consumer of this message in the swift app, which would be responsible for closing the current SLD view’s web view and/or reopening the new view’s web view_{color}

The {{handleLinkNavigation}} function (lines 1158-1166) needs to send an iOS message in flowOnlyMode instead of just calling {{setActiveViewId}}.

*Current code:*

{code:javascript}const handleLinkNavigation = useCallback((targetViewId, targetNodeId) => {
  pendingCenterNodeRef.current = targetNodeId;
  if (setActiveViewId) {
    setActiveViewId(targetViewId);
  }
}, [setActiveViewId]);{code}

*Updated code:*

{code:javascript}const handleLinkNavigation = useCallback((targetViewId, targetNodeId) => {
  if (flowOnlyMode) {
    // In iOS flowOnlyMode, send message to Swift to handle navigation
    sendMessage("graphUpdate", {
      type: "navigateToView",
      payload: { targetViewId, targetNodeId }
    });
  } else {
    // In web mode, handle locally
    pendingCenterNodeRef.current = targetNodeId;
    if (setActiveViewId) {
      setActiveViewId(targetViewId);
    }
  }
}, [flowOnlyMode, setActiveViewId]);{code}

*File:* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/utils/iosMessageHandlers.js}}

Add new message handler function:

{code:javascript}export const sendNavigateToView = (targetViewId, targetNodeId) => {
  sendMessage("graphUpdate", {
    type: "navigateToView",
    payload: { targetViewId, targetNodeId }
  });
};{code}

