h1. SLD Links Implementation Plan

h2. Overview

Implement SLD Links - navigational nodes (80x80 circles) that create two-way links between different SLD views, allowing users to jump to related assets in other views.

----

h2. Database Schema

{code:sql}CREATE TABLE sld_links (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    source_sld_view_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES sld_views(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    target_sld_view_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES sld_views(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    source_x FLOAT,
    source_y FLOAT,
    target_x FLOAT,
    target_y FLOAT,
    source_node_id UUID REFERENCES nodes(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
    target_node_id UUID REFERENCES nodes(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
    is_deleted BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),
    modified_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Indexes for common queries
CREATE INDEX ix_sld_links_source_view ON sld_links(source_sld_view_id);
CREATE INDEX ix_sld_links_target_view ON sld_links(target_sld_view_id);{code}

*Notes:*

* Terminal IDs derived from the edge connecting source_node and target_node (not stored)
* Two-way links: creating one auto-creates the inverse
* {{source_x/y}} and {{target_x/y}} store positions in respective views

----

