h3. Phase 8: Bug Fix - Loading Spinner

h4. 8.1 Issue Analysis

Current code sets {{isLoadingView(true)}} on view change but clears it very quickly (50ms delay). The data might already be cached, causing the spinner to flash too briefly.

h4. 8.2 Solution

*Modify:* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/GraphEditor.jsx}}

# Add minimum display time for loading spinner (300ms)
# Ensure fitView happens AFTER spinner is hidden

{code:javascript}// Track when loading started
const loadingStartTimeRef = useRef(null);

// When setting loading to true
useEffect(() => {
  if (activeViewId changed) {
    setIsLoadingView(true);
    loadingStartTimeRef.current = Date.now();
  }
}, [activeViewId]);

// When clearing loading state
const clearLoadingState = () => {
  const minDisplayTime = 300;
  const elapsed = Date.now() - loadingStartTimeRef.current;
  const remaining = Math.max(0, minDisplayTime - elapsed);

  setTimeout(() => {
    setIsLoadingView(false);
    // fitView here
  }, remaining);
};{code}

