h2. Key Points

# *Call order matters*: {{undoRedoDragStart()}} captures current positions BEFORE changes, {{undoRedoDragEnd()}} saves that snapshot to history
# *Guard with if checks*: The functions may be undefined if not passed, so guard calls
# *Timing for distribute*: Since {{handleDistributeNodes}} uses {{setTimeout}}, the {{undoRedoDragEnd()}} call should be inside the timeout after {{setNodes}}
# *No persistence changes needed*: Undo/redo only affects React state; persistence happens separately

