h1. Plan: Add Y-Value Synchronization to Straighten Downstream

h2. Overview

Modify the {{straightenDownstream}} function to also sync Y values, placing each row 500px below the previous one. For groups with multiple outbound paths, all nodes at the same depth should share the same Y value.

h2. Current Behavior

* Only aligns X positions (nodes get source's X coordinate)
* Y positions remain unchanged
* Works recursively but doesn't track depth/row level

h2. Target Behavior

* Align X positions (existing behavior)
* *New*: Set Y positions based on row/depth level
* Each row is 500px below the previous
* For groups: multiple downstream paths share Y values per row
* Row 0 = direct children of source, Row 1 = their children, etc.

h2. File to Modify

{{/Users/ericehlert/projects/eg-pz/eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/hooks/useDagreLayout.jsx}}

h2. Implementation Steps

h3. Step 1: Add Row Spacing Constant

Add at the top of the function:

{code:javascript}const ROW_SPACING = 500; // Pixels between rows{code}

h3. Step 2: Replace getDescendants with Level-Aware Function

Replace the current {{getDescendants}} helper with a new {{buildLevelMap}} function that:

* Returns a Map where key = depth level (0, 1, 2, ...) and value = array of {node, xPosition}
* Tracks depth as it traverses
* For groups: starts from each child's downstream connections

h3. Step 3: Update Group Node Logic (lines 726-770)

Change from:

# For each child, process its downstream recursively
# Set X to child's absolute X, keep Y unchanged

To:

# Get the source node's Y position as the base
# Build a level map for all downstream nodes across all children
# For each level, set Y = baseY + (level + 1) * ROW_SPACING
# Keep X logic the same (match child's absolute X)

h3. Step 4: Update Regular Node Logic (lines 771-805)

Change from:

# Process downstream recursively
# Set X to source X, keep Y unchanged

To:

# Get the source node's Y position as the base
# Build a level map for all downstream nodes
# For each level, set Y = baseY + (level + 1) * ROW_SPACING
# Keep X logic the same (match source X)

h2. Detailed Code Changes

h3. New Helper Function

{code:javascript}// Build a map of depth level -> nodes at that level
// Returns: Map<number, Array<{node, xPosition}>>
const buildLevelMap = (startNodeIds, xPositionMap) => {
  const levelMap = new Map();
  const visited = new Set();

  const traverse = (nodeId, level, xPos) => {
    if (visited.has(nodeId)) return;
    visited.add(nodeId);

    const node = nodes.find(n => n.id === nodeId);
    if (!node || node.parentId) return; // Skip group children

    if (!levelMap.has(level)) {
      levelMap.set(level, []);
    }
    levelMap.get(level).push({ node, xPosition: xPos });

    // Find downstream and recurse
    edges.forEach(edge => {
      if (edge.source === nodeId) {
        traverse(edge.target, level + 1, xPos);
      }
    });
  };

  // Start traversal from each start node
  startNodeIds.forEach(({ nodeId, xPos }) => {
    edges.forEach(edge => {
      if (edge.source === nodeId) {
        traverse(edge.target, 0, xPos);
      }
    });
  });

  return levelMap;
};{code}

h3. Updated Position Assignment

{code:javascript}const baseY = sourceNode.position.y;

// Build level map then assign positions
levelMap.forEach((nodesAtLevel, level) => {
  const rowY = baseY + (level + 1) * ROW_SPACING;
  nodesAtLevel.forEach(({ node, xPosition }) => {
    if (!processedDownstream.has(node.id)) {
      processedDownstream.add(node.id);
      newPositions[node.id] = {
        x: xPosition,
        y: rowY,
      };
    }
  });
});{code}

