h1. Plan: Enhance "Distribute Children" with Downstream-Based Ordering

h2. Summary

Enhance the existing {{handleDistributeNodes}} function to order child nodes based on their downstream connections' effective x-coordinates, and fix y-positioning so nodes touch the midpoint line.

h2. Requirements

# *Order by downstream effective-x*: Children should be arranged left-to-right based on their downstream node's x position
# *View-aware coordinates*: Use view-specific coordinates when in a view, nodes table coordinates when in "all nodes" view
# *Effective-x calculation*: If downstream node has a parent_id, use the parent's x; otherwise use the downstream node's x
# *Edge handling*:
#* Nodes with outbound edges: ordered by downstream effective-x
#* Nodes with inbound only (no outbound): placed in first half of slots
#* Nodes with no edges: placed at end of slots
# *Y positioning* (node height = 80px, group height = dynamic):
#* Bottom row nodes: top border touches midpoint (y = groupHeight/2)
#* Top row nodes: bottom border touches midpoint (y = groupHeight/2 - 80)

h2. File to Modify

{{/Users/ericehlert/projects/eg-pz/eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/hooks/useSelectionHandlers.jsx}}

h2. Implementation

h3. Step 1: Add helper function to get downstream effective-x

Add before {{handleDistributeNodes}} (~line 657):

{code:javascript}// Helper to get the effective x-coordinate for ordering based on downstream connection
const getDownstreamEffectiveX = useCallback((childNodeId) => {
  // Find outbound edge from this child
  const outboundEdge = edges?.find(edge => edge.source === childNodeId);
  if (!outboundEdge) return null;

  // Find the target (downstream) node
  const targetNode = nodes.find(n => n.id === outboundEdge.target);
  if (!targetNode) return null;

  // If target has a parent, use parent's x position (effective x)
  // Otherwise use the target's own x position
  if (targetNode.parentId) {
    const parentNode = nodes.find(n => n.id === targetNode.parentId);
    if (parentNode) {
      // Use positionAbsolute if available (view-aware), else position
      return parentNode.positionAbsolute?.x ?? parentNode.position?.x ?? parentNode.x ?? null;
    }
  }

  // No parent - use target's own position
  return targetNode.positionAbsolute?.x ?? targetNode.position?.x ?? targetNode.x ?? null;
}, [nodes, edges]);{code}

h3. Step 2: Modify the ordering logic in {{handleDistributeNodes}}

After classifying nodes into {{topRowNodes}} and {{bottomRowNodes}} (after line 694), add sorting logic:

{code:javascript}// Sort each row by downstream effective-x
// Category order: 1=has downstream, 0=has upstream only (no downstream), 2=no edges
const sortByDownstream = (rowNodes) => {
  return [...rowNodes].sort((a, b) => {
    const aHasOutbound = edges?.some(e => e.source === a.id);
    const bHasOutbound = edges?.some(e => e.source === b.id);
    const aHasInbound = edges?.some(e => e.target === a.id);
    const bHasInbound = edges?.some(e => e.target === b.id);

    // Determine category: 0=upstream only, 1=has outbound, 2=no edges
    const getCategory = (hasOut, hasIn) => {
      if (hasOut) return 1;
      if (hasIn) return 0; // upstream only goes first
      return 2; // no edges goes last
    };

    const aCat = getCategory(aHasOutbound, aHasInbound);
    const bCat = getCategory(bHasOutbound, bHasInbound);

    // Sort by category first
    if (aCat !== bCat) return aCat - bCat;

    // Within same category, sort by downstream effective-x (or current x if no downstream)
    const aEffectiveX = getDownstreamEffectiveX(a.id) ?? (a.positionAbsolute?.x ?? a.position?.x ?? 0);
    const bEffectiveX = getDownstreamEffectiveX(b.id) ?? (b.positionAbsolute?.x ?? b.position?.x ?? 0);

    return aEffectiveX - bEffectiveX;
  });
};

// Apply sorting to both rows
const sortedTopRowNodes = sortByDownstream(topRowNodes);
const sortedBottomRowNodes = sortByDownstream(bottomRowNodes);{code}

h3. Step 3: Enforce minimum group height and update Y positioning

Replace the group height calculation (around line 703):

{code:javascript}const newGroupHeight = Math.max(160, groupNode.style?.height ?? 160); // Minimum 160px{code}

Replace the current y-position logic (lines 747-755):

{code:javascript}// Y positioning: nodes should touch the midpoint line
