h3. Overview

Users cannot add work unit scope items to standard quotes without linking to a node. The frontend validation incorrectly requires either a {{node_id}} OR a {{procedure_id}}, but the database and backend allow both to be null (for custom scope items with just a description).

h3. Root Cause

The frontend validation in {{WorkUnitsTab.jsx}} at lines 699-704 has overly strict validation that doesn't account for the {{addLineMode}}:

{code:javascript}// Line 699-704 - BUG: This is mode-agnostic
if (!newLineData.procedure_id && !newLineData.node_id) {
  alert('Please select at least a node or a procedure');
  return;
}{code}

Meanwhile, the button disable logic at lines 3129-3133 IS mode-aware:

{code:javascript}disabled={
  addLineLoading ||
  (addLineMode === 'procedure' && !newLineData.procedure_id) ||
  (addLineMode === 'custom' && !newLineData.description && !newLineData.node_id)
}{code}

*The mismatch:* In custom mode, the button enables when description is provided (even without node_id), but validation fails because it requires node_id OR procedure_id.

h3. Technical Approach

h4. File to Modify

{{/eg-pz-frontend/src/components/WorkUnitsTab.jsx}}

h4. Change Required

*Update* {{handleAddNewLine()}} validation (lines 699-704) to match the button disable logic:

*Current (lines 699-704):*

{code:javascript}const handleAddNewLine = async () => {
  // Procedure is now optional
  if (!newLineData.procedure_id && !newLineData.node_id) {
    alert('Please select at least a node or a procedure');
    return;
  }{code}

*Fixed:*

{code:javascript}const handleAddNewLine = async () => {
  // Validate based on mode
  if (addLineMode === 'procedure' && !newLineData.procedure_id) {
    alert('Please select a procedure');
    return;
  }
  if (addLineMode === 'custom' && !newLineData.description?.trim() && !newLineData.node_id) {
    alert('Please enter a description or select an asset');
    return;
  }{code}

This makes the validation consistent with the button disable logic - in custom mode, either description OR node_id is required.

h3. Acceptance Criteria

* [ ] Users can add custom scope items with just a description (no node, no procedure)
* [ ] Users can add custom scope items with just a node (no description, no procedure)
* [ ] Users can still add scope items from procedures (requires procedure selection)
* [ ] Node selection remains optional in procedure mode
* [ ] Backend accepts the requests without node_id

