h2. Refactoring Plan

h1. Fix: Auto-distribute children when adding groups via Lineage

h2. Problem

When adding nodes to a view from the "Manage Asset's Lineage" option, groups that are pulled in do not have their children auto-distributed. However, this works correctly when:

# A single asset is pulled in via "Search & Pull" from the context menu
# An asset is pulled in via search & pull

h2. Root Cause

The issue is a *timing race condition* in the existing auto-distribution code.

*Existing code in* {{GraphEditor.jsx:3990-4014}}:

{code:javascript}onAssetsChanged={(addedAssets) => {
  if (activeViewId && activeViewId !== 'all') {
    fetchSldViews(sldId);
    const currentView = activeViewId;
    setActiveViewId(null);              // Step 1: Clear view (100ms before next step)
    setTimeout(() => {
      setActiveViewId(currentView);     // Step 2: Restore view (triggers ASYNC fetch)
      if (addedAssets?.length > 0) {
        setTimeout(() => {              // Step 3: 300ms later, try to distribute
          const groupIds = addedAssets.filter(a => a.type === 'group').map(a => a.id);
          groupIds.forEach(groupId => handleDistributeNodesRef.current(groupId));
        }, 300);
      }
    }, 100);
  }
}}{code}

*The Problem:*

* Step 2 triggers {{fetchViewFullData}} which is an async network call
* Step 3 runs 300ms after Step 2, but the network fetch may not be complete
* When {{handleDistributeNodes}} runs, the nodes may not be in React Flow state yet

*Why Search & Pull Works:*

* Directly adds nodes to React Flow state via {{setNodes(nds => [...nds, ...newNodes])}}
* 300ms delay is sufficient for React to process the synchronous state update
* No async network call needed

h2. Solution

Use a ref to track pending group distributions, then trigger distribution when the data actually loads (via the existing {{sldNodes}} useEffect in App.jsx).

This is a *frontend-only fix* that doesn't require backend changes.

h2. Implementation Plan

h3. Step 1: Add a ref to track pending group distributions

*File:* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/GraphEditor.jsx}}

Add a ref to store group IDs that need distribution after a view refresh:

{code:javascript}const pendingGroupDistributionRef = useRef([]);{code}

h3. Step 2: Update onAssetsChanged to store pending groups

*File:* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/GraphEditor.jsx}}

In the {{onAssetsChanged}} callback (lines 3990-4014), instead of trying to distribute in a setTimeout:

# Store the group IDs in {{pendingGroupDistributionRef}}
# Let the view toggle/refresh happen
# Remove the inner setTimeout that tries to distribute

{code:javascript}onAssetsChanged={(addedAssets) => {
  if (activeViewId && activeViewId !== 'all') {
    fetchSldViews(sldId);
    const currentView = activeViewId;

    // Store group IDs for distribution after data loads
    if (addedAssets?.length > 0) {
      const groupIds = addedAssets
        .filter(a => a.type === 'group')
        .map(a => a.id);
      if (groupIds.length > 0) {
        pendingGroupDistributionRef.current = groupIds;
      }
    }

    // Toggle view to trigger refresh
    setActiveViewId(null);
    setTimeout(() => {
      setActiveViewId(currentView);
    }, 100);
  }
}}{code}

h3. Step 3: Add useEffect to trigger distribution when data loads

*File:* {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/components/GraphEditor.jsx}}

Add a useEffect that watches {{nodes}} and checks for pending distributions:

{code:javascript}// Trigger pending group distributions when data loads
useEffect(() => {
  if (pendingGroupDistributionRef.current.length > 0 && nodes.length > 0) {
    const groupIds = pendingGroupDistributionRef.current;

    // Check if the groups are now in the nodes array
    const groupsReady = groupIds.every(id => nodes.some(n => n.id === id));

    if (groupsReady) {
      // Clear pending immediately to prevent re-triggering
      pendingGroupDistributionRef.current = [];

      // Distribute after React processes state
      setTimeout(() => {
        groupIds.forEach(groupId => {
          handleDistributeNodesRef.current(groupId);
        });
      }, 300);
    }
  }
}, [nodes]);{code}

