h1. Fix: Distribute Children Not Saving Group Size to Backend

h2. Problem

When "Distribute Children" is executed, the group node resizes correctly in the UI but the new width/height is not persisted to the backend.

h2. Root Cause

In {{useSelectionHandlers.jsx}}, line 764 calls:

{code:javascript}queuePositionUpdate(node.id, node.position, null, newGroupWidth);{code}

But {{queuePositionUpdate}} (line 76) only accepts 3 parameters:

{code:javascript}(nodeId, position, parentId = null){code}

The {{newGroupWidth}} parameter is *silently ignored*. The backend API ({{putNodePosition}}) does support width/height, but the batching system doesn't pass it through.

h2. Solution

Extend the batching system to support width/height parameters:

h3. File: {{eg-pz-frontend/src/sld/src/hooks/useSelectionHandlers.jsx}}

*Step 1*: Update {{queuePositionUpdate}} to accept an optional 4th parameter for additional fields:

{code:javascript}const queuePositionUpdate = useCallback(
  (nodeId, position, parentId = null, additionalFields = null) => {
    pendingPositionUpdates.current.set(nodeId, {
      nodeId,
      position,
      parentId,
      additionalFields,  // Add this field
    });
    // ... rest unchanged
  },
  [sendBatchedPositionUpdates]
);{code}

*Step 2*: Update {{sendBatchedPositionUpdates}} to pass {{additionalFields}} to {{putNodePosition}}:

{code:javascript}// Normal mode (all nodes view) - save to nodes table
updates.forEach((update) => {
  putNodePosition(
    update.nodeId,
    update.position,
    update.parentId ?? null,
    update.additionalFields  // Add this parameter
  );
});{code}

*Step 3*: Update the call at line 764 to pass width AND height:

{code:javascript}queuePositionUpdate(node.id, node.position, null, { width: newGroupWidth, height: newGroupHeight });{code}

